entry.title: Going to tag 0.9.2 final
entry.summary: In an email exchange on June 14, 2014, a user named Un Ix suggested offering a prize for anyone who could find malicious strings within the next hour. In response, Wladimir cautioned against focusing on such a task and instead suggested looking out for icebergs over wrongly arranged deck chairs. The conversation does not provide any further context or information.
